<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="damage-n">damage <strong><em>n</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /'dæmɪdʒ/    美 /'dæmɪdʒ/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-u">1.★ <strong>[U] 损害；损坏；损失</strong></h4>
<p>harm or injury caused when sth is broken or spoiled：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>storm damage to</strong> the trees
暴风雨对树木造成的损害</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He was hit by a car and suffered serious <strong>brain damage</strong>. 
他被车撞了，脑部严重损伤。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>do / cause damage to:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The problem is clear: man has done great damage to his home over the years.
问题显而易见：多年来，人类已经严重破坏了自己的家园。</p><footer>2008 全国</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The heavy rain had caused <strong>serious damage</strong> to the roof.
大雨严重损坏了房顶。</p></div>

<h4 id="2c">2.<strong>[C] [常用复数] 损害赔偿金：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He was ordered to pay damages of $30,000.
他被责令支付3万美元的损害赔偿金。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>The accident caused some <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (损坏) to my car, but it’s nothing serious.  （2013 辽宁改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. damage  </p></div>